There is now a passage I don't fully understand, including formulae 'Si vigilia epiphaniae dominica evenerit sabbato praecedente...', but this surely is the same as 'octave of Innocents if a Saturday' which we have had already --- the vigil of Epiphany is 5 Jan, so if that is a Sunday the preceding Saturday will be 4 Jan, which is the Octave of the Innocents.  This present passage includes inter alia the lessons of a third nocturn, with respond incipits.  Much of the remainder of fols.28v-29r concern conditionals.  I specify here only that service (lauds) with a full chant item.


